        "Emray": { 
            url: "https://open.spotify.com/artist/25gSGW8P5WC9C3vTSOYS0h", 
            color: "rgba(87, 51, 255, 0.1)" 
        },
    }
};

---

<Layout>
    <div class="layout">
        <h2>About Me</h2>
        <div class="box-special">
            <p>
                I'm a small programmer who likes doing things on their own, though also often works with other people in either teams or just in collaboration!<br/><br/>
    
                <strong><em>Very</em></strong> interested in iOS/tvOS/macOS-related software, really anything Apple. First took interest several years ago with a small SE and now since I've taken interest, I've built a lot of software that people like to use :D
            </p>
        </div>
        <p>
            As shown above, yes I'm a programmer who likes all stuff Apple. I have a lot of projects that I've worked on which you can find on my Github, some of which (mainly organizations) I do own to some extent and related to (of course) Apple.<br/><br/>
            
            A lot of the projects I have are often open-source.
        </p>


        <h2>My Skills</h2>
        <Skills/>


        <h2>My Hobbies</h2>
        <p>
            I play a lot of games, mainly on my computer. These mainly consists of games which just allow me to do whatever I feel like without some straight linear path. 
        </p>
        <div style="display: flex;flex-wrap: wrap;">
            {
                Object.keys(profileData.games).map((item) => (
                    <a href={profileData.games[item].url} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style={{ textDecoration: 'none' }}>
                        <div class="contact-pill" style={{ backgroundColor: profileData.games[item].color, border: `1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1)` }}>
                            {item} ↗
                        </div>
                    </a>
                ))
            }
        </div>
        <p>
            I also do a lot of biking on my own, also love trying to make food with other people! 
        </p>


        <h2>Musical Artists I Love</h2>
        <p>
            I listen to a lot of music! Mainly from Spotify, but I also listen to music from other sources. Here are some of the artists!
        </p>
        <div style="display: flex;flex-wrap: wrap;">
            {
                Object.keys(profileData.songs).map((item) => (
                    <a href={profileData.songs[item].url} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style={{ textDecoration: 'none' }}>
                        <div class="contact-pill" style={{ backgroundColor: profileData.songs[item].color, border: `1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1)` }}>
                            {item} ↗
                        </div>
                    </a>
                ))
            }
        </div>
        <p>
            I listen to music from artists which are more unknown, honestly I find more joy in that than traditional mainstream artists and music.
        </p>
        <a href="https://www.last.fm/user/fivepetals" style="display: flex;flex-wrap: wrap;">
            <div class="contact-pill">
                Check out my LastFM ↗
            </div>
        </a>
        
        <Footer/>
    </div>
</Layout>
